    "subtype": "weapon",
    "text": "A bec de corbin is a spiked polearm that uses a hammer head to help balance the spike. The hammer portion can be used as a secondary striking surface, while the spike or fluke is specially designed to punch through armor and shields.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 488,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "1e43c7605c9909b20b487f7dd05b5cee",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "shields",
            "href": "Shields.aspx",
            "name": "shields",
            "type": "link"
          },
          {
            "alt": "animated objects",
            "aonid": 360,
            "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
            "name": "animated objects",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Razing",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "1.1",
              "aonid": 227,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "1.1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
              "aonid": 227,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core 2",
            "page": 274,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Razing weapons are particularly good at damaging objects, structures, and vehicles. Whenever you deal damage to an object (including shields and animated objects), structure, or vehicle with a razing weapon, the object takes an amount of additional damage equal to double the number of weapon damage dice.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 192,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "1d6143e399ba5d4085ca236a97cf860c",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Reach",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 283,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This weapon can be used to attack enemies up to 10 feet away instead of only adjacent enemies. For creatures with reach, the weapon increases their reach by 5 feet.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 193,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "6cd7af0b11cadecab9bad5582f02196b",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Shove",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 283,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "You can use this weapon to Shove with the Athletics skill even if you don\u2019t have a free hand. This uses the weapon\u2019s reach (if different from your own) and adds the weapon\u2019s item bonus to attack rolls as an item bonus to the Athletics check. If you critically fail a check to Shove using the weapon, you can drop the weapon to take the effects of a failure instead of a critical failure.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 200,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "ca5b7a642aef726cc9055981ca84f89d",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Versatile",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 283,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A versatile weapon can be used to deal a different type of damage than its listed type. This trait indicates the alternate damage type. For instance, a piercing weapon with versatile S can deal piercing or slashing damage. You choose the damage type each time you attack.",
        "type": "trait",
        "value": "B"
      }
    ],
    "type": "stat_block"
  },
  "type": "weapon"
